                            <comment id="17051458" author="hossman" created="Wed, 4 Mar 2020 17:47:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ichattopadhyaya&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ichattopadhyaya&quot;&gt;ichattopadhyaya&lt;/a&gt;: you removed this in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-13394&quot; title=&quot;Change default GC from CMS to G1&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-13394&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-13394&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;  , i assume unintentionally? ... any objection to adding it back?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17051473" author="ichattopadhyaya" created="Wed, 4 Mar 2020 18:01:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ouch, just realized that I had omitted it. I think I mistook it for some CMS specific parameter as it was under GC_TUNE.&lt;br/&gt;
No objection to bringing it back (so long as it doesn&apos;t go back to GC_TUNE again. Thanks Hoss!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17051719" author="hossman" created="Thu, 5 Mar 2020 01:12:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching proposed fix that adds &lt;tt&gt;-XX:-OmitStackTraceInFastThrow&lt;/tt&gt; directly to SOLR_START_OPTS with a comment, users that don&apos;t care about having readable error messages can override by setting &lt;tt&gt;-XX:+OmitStackTraceInFastThrow&lt;/tt&gt; in SOLR_OPTS, or with the &quot;-a&quot; command line option, etc...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;feedback (particularly of the solr.cmd changes i have no ability to test) requested asap in the hopes that we can included this fix in 8.5.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
